Cardio Good Fitness Project¶

Key analysis objectives of the Project¶

  1. Explore the dataset to identify differences between customers of each product.
  2. Explore relationships between the different attributes of customers.
  3. Find new insights which could be relevant for the business.

Data Context¶

The data is for customers of the treadmill product(s) of a retail store called Cardio Good Fitness. It contains the following variables

  1. Product - the model no. of the treadmill
  2. Age - in no of years, of the customer
  3. Gender - of the customer
  4. Education - in no. of years, of the customer
  5. Marital Status - of the customer
  6. Usage - Avg. # times the customer wants to use the treadmill every week
  7. Fitness - Self rated fitness score of the customer (5 - very fit, 1 - very unfit)
  8. Income - of the customer
  9. Miles- expected to run

Customer Profile based on the data set:

  1. Total number of customers are 180.
  2. Total number of products used by the customers are 3.
  3. TM195 is most used product (80 customers)
  4. Mean age of customer is 28 years (Min 18 years and Max 50 years)
  5. There are more male customers (104) than females (76)
  6. Mean education of the customer is around 15 years.The range varies from 12 years to 21 years.
  7. Customer usage ranges from 2 to 7 and mean usage value is 3.4
  8. Mean fitness of customer in scale of 1 to 5 is 3.3
  9. Income of customer ranges from approx 29.5K to 104.5k where avg income is approx 53.7k
  10. Miles run by the customer ranges from 21 to 360. Mean usage in approx 103 miles.

Checking for missing values¶

In [10]:
def missingvaluecheck(dat): #function to find missing values within the dataset
    calc_total = dat.isnull().sum().sort_values(ascending=False) #Checking for total null values
    calc_percent = (dat.isnull().sum()/dat.isnull().count()).sort_values(ascending=False) #checking percentage
    data_missing = pd.concat([calc_total, calc_percent], axis=1, keys=['Total', 'Percent']) #to display missing data count and percentage
    return data_missing # return the dataframe

Insights and Recommendations:¶

  1. TM195 is most popular product
  2. The products are popular with younger adults. More focused assessment should be done to find out why the products are not very popular with age group beyond 42 years
  3. Products ate popular with customers with no of years of education between 14 and 18. This should be considered for future sales target
  4. The products are more preferred by the customers who have partners
  5. The target age group that can result into more sales range 23 to 33 years
  6. TM798 is unpopular with Females. More focused assessment should be done to find out the reasons
  7. Most fit people are using TM798. People with average fitness prefer TM195 and TM498
  8. TM195 has highest usability
  9. People using TM798 run more number of miles
  10. TM195 and TM498 are popular with customers having income 30K to 70K. TM798 is more popular with customer of income group 70K and above
  11. TM195 and TM498 are popular with People with salary less than 70K TM798 is popular with people having Income more than 45K People with income greater than 70K but TM798
  12. Income of customer ranges from approx 29.5K to 104.5k where avg income is approx 53.7 k
  13. TM798 is clearly used by separate set of customer considering the age and income. There is less overlap with customer of TM195 and TM498
